533
00:29:22,854 --> 00:29:23,979
So tell me,

534
00:29:24,104 --> 00:29:27,854
did you make good of the chance?

535
00:29:29,354 --> 00:29:30,521
She was the one doing the dance…

536
00:29:30,604 --> 00:29:31,646
Where?

537
00:29:31,979 --> 00:29:33,854
I've seen quite a few verses
in your posts.

538
00:29:34,979 --> 00:29:35,979
You write too?

539
00:29:36,687 --> 00:29:37,604
Why?

540
00:29:38,312 --> 00:29:39,646
Don't I look the type?

541
00:29:41,396 --> 00:29:42,479
It's not that.

542
00:29:45,687 --> 00:29:49,437
My dad loved verses.

543
00:29:49,979 --> 00:29:51,396
Watch out…
or you'll fall to your death in vain,

544
00:29:51,479 --> 00:29:52,937
and I'll spend my youth rotting in jail.

545
00:29:55,396 --> 00:29:56,646
If I wanted to die,

546
00:29:57,479 --> 00:30:00,896
I would've drowned myself
in my pool already.

547
00:30:09,062 --> 00:30:10,521
You know what your tragedy is?

548
00:30:12,562 --> 00:30:13,521
There's a huge ocean out there.

549
00:30:13,604 --> 00:30:15,979
But you want to die in
your 20x20 swimming pool.

550
00:30:17,437 --> 00:30:18,396
Learn from me.

551
00:30:18,854 --> 00:30:20,187
I live in a 10x10 room.

552
00:30:20,854 --> 00:30:22,437
But I live life king-size,
from Virar to Churchgate.

553
00:30:30,771 --> 00:30:35,062
Show me your life then,
from Virar to Churchgate…

554
00:30:38,062 --> 00:30:40,646
Of course.
Whenever you say.

555
00:30:42,479 --> 00:30:43,896
I'll come pick you up.

556
00:31:03,729 --> 00:31:04,604
This one?

557
00:31:05,937 --> 00:31:06,937
Yeah.

558
00:31:10,521 --> 00:31:11,437
Thanks.

559
00:31:16,562 --> 00:31:17,687
I had a good time.

560
00:31:18,812 --> 00:31:19,729
I mean, I enjoyed myself.

561
00:31:21,646 --> 00:31:23,521
Hit me up if you feel like it.

562
00:31:26,187 --> 00:31:27,521
Not that I'm waiting or something.

563
00:31:31,271 --> 00:31:32,229
Ms. Vanity…

564
00:31:33,812 --> 00:31:35,062
I don't have your number.

565
00:31:37,812 --> 00:31:39,229
I'll slide into your DM.

566
00:31:43,937 --> 00:31:45,187
If I feel like it.

567
00:32:13,521 --> 00:32:14,604
She didn't text, did she?

568
00:32:14,687 --> 00:32:16,187
Told you she wouldn't.

569
00:32:16,271 --> 00:32:17,646
Why are you waiting on her?

570
00:32:19,979 --> 00:32:20,854
She texted, didn't she?

571
00:32:20,937 --> 00:32:22,437
Told you she would!

572
00:32:22,896 --> 00:32:24,562
What's this?
She dropped a location pin.

573
00:32:27,562 --> 00:32:28,979
Challenge accepted, bro!

574
00:32:29,062 --> 00:32:29,937
- I got to run!
- Where to?

575
00:32:30,021 --> 00:32:30,937
Catch you in the evening.

576
00:32:31,021 --> 00:32:32,771
- Where are you headed, pumpkin?
- I'll fill you in later.

577
00:33:02,062 --> 00:33:05,271
Never thought you'd hit me up.

578
00:33:08,771 --> 00:33:10,312
Were you waiting for it?

579
00:33:10,396 --> 00:33:11,396
Not really.

580
00:33:11,812 --> 00:33:12,771
You know my friend, Fabric?

581
00:33:14,021 --> 00:33:17,187
He said a girl like you won't
be interested in a guy like me.

582
00:33:19,146 --> 00:33:20,354
Not sure if you're my type.

583
00:33:20,896 --> 00:33:22,271
I always bet on hope.

584
00:33:25,437 --> 00:33:26,354
And in any case,

585
00:33:26,896 --> 00:33:29,104
I have no interest
in becoming your type.

586
00:33:30,146 --> 00:33:31,937
But there's a chance
you could become like me.

587
00:34:00,062 --> 00:34:04,646
Stealthily and slyly
When our eyes lock, what happens?

588
00:34:06,354 --> 00:34:08,812
When the crazy heart beats

589
00:34:08,896 --> 00:34:11,521
For the first time, what happens?

590
00:34:13,687 --> 00:34:15,687
Strangers become

591
00:34:15,771 --> 00:34:18,021
Lovers, lovers, lovers

592
00:34:18,312 --> 00:34:20,271
Unknowingly and inadvertently

593
00:34:20,354 --> 00:34:22,521
They fall in love

594
00:34:22,604 --> 00:34:23,646
What is this?

595
00:34:23,729 --> 00:34:24,729
How does it happen?

596
00:34:24,812 --> 00:34:26,146
Nobody knows that

597
00:34:29,146 --> 00:34:33,062
Oh, wow! Amazing!
This is a sick phone!

598
00:34:33,146 --> 00:34:34,354
For you, this is chump change.

599
00:34:34,937 --> 00:34:36,812
Flow, I'm not your sugar mommy.

600
00:34:36,896 --> 00:34:37,771
Then become one.

601
00:34:38,604 --> 00:34:40,479
- I really don't have an ego.
- So what?

602
00:34:40,896 --> 00:34:42,854
You're only interested
in me because I'm rich?

603
00:34:42,937 --> 00:34:44,604
When I was a kid, I'd decided

604
00:34:44,687 --> 00:34:46,312
my girlfriend had to be
from a posh part of downtown.

605
00:34:46,687 --> 00:34:47,646
Girlfriend?

606
00:34:48,312 --> 00:34:50,104
- So it's official now?
- Let's do it.

607
00:34:50,187 --> 00:34:51,562
Zero percent toxic.

608
00:34:52,146 --> 00:34:53,521
Hundred percent satisfaction.

609
00:34:54,062 --> 00:34:55,479
Or a full refund is guaranteed.

610
00:34:57,479 --> 00:34:58,562
What do you say?

611
00:34:59,937 --> 00:35:01,187
Should I put it on my status?

612
00:35:04,229 --> 00:35:08,687
Stealthily and slyly
When our eyes lock, what happens?

613
00:35:18,812 --> 00:35:21,104
I wandered

614
00:35:21,187 --> 00:35:23,437
All over town

615
00:35:23,937 --> 00:35:27,354
I saw many beauties

616
00:35:27,979 --> 00:35:30,271
I am quite sure

617
00:35:30,354 --> 00:35:32,521
Nobody anywhere

618
00:35:32,937 --> 00:35:36,354
Is like you

619
00:35:37,312 --> 00:35:39,271
It makes the heart go crazy

620
00:35:39,354 --> 00:35:41,896
What is that union?

621
00:35:41,979 --> 00:35:43,896
It's now that I know

622
00:35:43,979 --> 00:35:46,354
What first love really is

623
00:35:46,521 --> 00:35:48,437
Strangers become

624
00:35:48,521 --> 00:35:50,854
Lovers, lovers, lovers

625
00:35:51,146 --> 00:35:53,021
Unknowingly and inadvertently

626
00:35:53,104 --> 00:35:55,312
They fall in love

627
00:35:55,396 --> 00:35:56,437
What is this?

628
00:35:56,521 --> 00:35:57,562
- How does it happen?
- So, what do you think?

629
00:35:57,646 --> 00:35:59,104
Nobody knows that

630
00:35:59,896 --> 00:36:02,021
Fabric and I set this up for you!

631
00:36:04,271 --> 00:36:05,646
Hey, hey, it’s getting away.

632
00:36:20,312 --> 00:36:22,604
My heart prays

633
00:36:22,687 --> 00:36:24,979
If I am destined for it

634
00:36:25,354 --> 00:36:28,479
Then your love is what I seek

635
00:36:29,812 --> 00:36:31,729
When you meet someone

636
00:36:31,812 --> 00:36:33,979
Who strikes the chord of your heart
Then what happens?

637
00:36:34,354 --> 00:36:36,271
When your breaths

638
00:36:36,354 --> 00:36:38,604
Start ringing, what is it?

639
00:36:38,896 --> 00:36:40,812
Strangers become

640
00:36:40,896 --> 00:36:43,187
Lovers, lovers, lovers

641
00:36:43,437 --> 00:36:45,312
Unknowingly and inadvertently

642
00:36:45,396 --> 00:36:47,646
They fall in love

643
00:36:47,729 --> 00:36:48,812
What is this?

644
00:36:48,896 --> 00:36:49,896
How does it happen?

645
00:36:49,979 --> 00:36:52,104
Nobody knows that

646
00:36:55,479 --> 00:36:59,187
Lyra was asking if we're both dating
or just like hooking up?

647
00:37:01,021 --> 00:37:02,062
What did you say?

648
00:37:02,187 --> 00:37:03,271
I said,

649
00:37:05,896 --> 00:37:07,562
"Have you gone nuts, homie?"

650
00:37:14,812 --> 00:37:15,687
Nice!

651
00:37:16,562 --> 00:37:17,562
Company matters.

652
00:37:20,687 --> 00:37:21,562
Homie.

653
00:37:25,062 --> 00:37:26,646
I hope you're not catching feelings.

654
00:37:27,062 --> 00:37:28,021
Are you crazy?

655
00:37:31,812 --> 00:37:33,396
You're casual too, right?

656
00:37:36,729 --> 00:37:40,187
If there's no future to us,
why am I wasting my time with you?

657
00:37:40,271 --> 00:37:41,187
Wait.

658
00:37:52,021 --> 00:37:52,896
Are you mad?

659
00:37:54,437 --> 00:37:55,937
Quit playing.
I can't swim.

660
00:37:56,021 --> 00:37:57,021
I could've drowned.

661
00:38:06,521 --> 00:38:08,229
I won't let you ever drown, Flow.

662
00:38:49,729 --> 00:38:52,396
Remember I told you about a girl?
Avani, my friend.

663
00:39:10,021 --> 00:39:11,937
Mom, hope it's not too spicy
for her.

664
00:39:12,021 --> 00:39:13,437
She is so pretty, right?

665
00:39:15,854 --> 00:39:17,771
Let's take a picture.

666
00:39:17,854 --> 00:39:19,187
I'm shy…

667
00:39:19,396 --> 00:39:20,396
Too good, Auntie.

668
00:39:20,687 --> 00:39:21,562
Thank you.

669
00:39:21,646 --> 00:39:22,646
Hope it's not too spicy.

670
00:39:22,729 --> 00:39:24,146
No, not at all.

671
00:39:24,312 --> 00:39:26,104
Even if it is,
she won't say it to your face.

672
00:39:26,187 --> 00:39:27,104
Just shut up.

673
00:39:27,687 --> 00:39:28,646
Water?

674
00:39:30,771 --> 00:39:32,562
Do you make poha at home?

675
00:39:32,937 --> 00:39:33,812
Sometimes.

676
00:39:34,062 --> 00:39:35,979
But not as tasty as this.

677
00:39:36,604 --> 00:39:39,271
You should try her snacks.

678
00:39:39,604 --> 00:39:40,937
From Nala Sopara to Borivali,

679
00:39:41,312 --> 00:39:44,312
Mom supplies snacks
to every chemist and grocery store.

680
00:39:44,896 --> 00:39:46,437
Under the brand "Kusum Vitthal".

681
00:39:46,979 --> 00:39:48,354
She's Ms. Vanity, sis.

682
00:39:49,146 --> 00:39:51,271
She won't promote
our snacks on her reels.

683
00:39:52,146 --> 00:39:54,021
Flow, don't underestimate me.

684
00:39:54,354 --> 00:39:56,646
Ms. Vanity can do anything.

685
00:39:57,479 --> 00:39:59,521
You just enjoy the fritters.
Okay?

686
00:40:00,646 --> 00:40:01,937
What can I say now?
I'm out of here.

687
00:40:30,687 --> 00:40:31,812
How do you like my mom?

688
00:40:33,479 --> 00:40:34,396
She's awesome.

689
00:40:34,812 --> 00:40:35,687
Isn't she?

690
00:40:36,354 --> 00:40:37,354
She takes after me.

691
00:40:42,062 --> 00:40:43,104
And how do you like my kingdom?

692
00:40:44,771 --> 00:40:47,729
Bet you don't get this view
from your bungalow terrace.

693
00:40:50,521 --> 00:40:52,187
I sit here and write all my tracks.

694
00:40:55,104 --> 00:40:56,771
When Mom starts yapping too much,

695
00:40:57,479 --> 00:40:58,562
I escape here.

696
00:41:01,396 --> 00:41:02,646
Where's your dad?

697
00:41:04,854 --> 00:41:06,604
He bailed when I was five.

698
00:41:09,479 --> 00:41:10,771
Sister says,

699
00:41:11,687 --> 00:41:13,312
Mom and Dad fought a lot.

700
00:41:14,729 --> 00:41:15,687
I don't remember much.

701
00:41:19,562 --> 00:41:21,229
Did you ever try to find him?

702
00:41:23,437 --> 00:41:27,021
Uncle saw him in Satara once.

703
00:41:29,229 --> 00:41:30,354
With a new family.

704
00:41:33,562 --> 00:41:34,562
He looked happy.

705
00:41:37,812 --> 00:41:39,271
Fate has its ways.

706
00:41:44,771 --> 00:41:45,979
Same story here.

707
00:41:46,521 --> 00:41:48,021
But your scene is different.

708
00:41:49,896 --> 00:41:51,062
Both your parents are gone.

709
00:41:58,146 --> 00:41:59,187
But…

710
00:41:59,729 --> 00:42:01,104
how was it before?

711
00:42:02,312 --> 00:42:03,854
Did they love you a lot?

712
00:42:12,729 --> 00:42:16,812
They fought too… like cats and dogs.

713
00:42:21,771 --> 00:42:22,729
I mean,

714
00:42:23,937 --> 00:42:26,521
it didn't faze Tara much or…

715
00:42:28,896 --> 00:42:29,812
I don't know.

716
00:42:30,771 --> 00:42:32,312
Maybe she was used to the drama.

717
00:42:37,312 --> 00:42:39,021
But whenever they fought,

718
00:42:40,979 --> 00:42:42,187
I used to bawl my eyes out.

719
00:42:47,812 --> 00:42:51,021
That day, too, they were yelling,

720
00:42:51,896 --> 00:42:53,396
and I started crying loudly.

721
00:42:54,146 --> 00:42:55,312
Like, like uncontrollably.

722
00:43:01,354 --> 00:43:03,062
Then to cheer me up,

723
00:43:04,437 --> 00:43:06,562
dad took us for a drive and…

724
00:43:10,854 --> 00:43:11,729
And?

725
00:43:44,562 --> 00:43:46,896
They both died in that car accident.

726
00:43:47,521 --> 00:43:48,521
But I survived.

727
00:44:04,979 --> 00:44:06,562
Come on, come on, come on!

728
00:44:34,271 --> 00:44:35,187
Hello!

729
00:44:36,437 --> 00:44:37,437
Is anyone there?

730
00:44:40,187 --> 00:44:41,104
Hello!

731
00:44:54,562 --> 00:44:55,771
Is anyone there?

732
00:44:57,646 --> 00:44:58,562
Avani!

733
00:44:59,896 --> 00:45:01,062
Help!

734
00:45:01,229 --> 00:45:02,271
Avani!

735
00:45:30,062 --> 00:45:32,646
I'm sorry, I panicked.
I didn't know what to do.

736
00:45:34,271 --> 00:45:35,437
You panic. You come to me.

737
00:45:36,396 --> 00:45:38,229
Why did you tell Di and Jeej?

738
00:45:38,687 --> 00:45:39,979
Avani!
Avani!

739
00:45:40,312 --> 00:45:42,396
- Come outside, I need to talk to you.
- Look what you've done.

740
00:45:44,771 --> 00:45:46,312
I'll take care of it, I'm sorry.

741
00:45:46,396 --> 00:45:48,479
Avani, open the door.
I need to talk to you.

742
00:45:51,646 --> 00:45:52,562
Is that the guy?

743
00:45:52,854 --> 00:45:53,729
Seriously, Avani?

744
00:45:55,521 --> 00:45:57,937
Please tell me you slept with him
out of some weird sense of pity.

745
00:45:58,437 --> 00:46:00,187
Ever heard of protection?

746
00:46:00,479 --> 00:46:01,354
Tara.

747
00:46:01,729 --> 00:46:02,979
Why are we even looking
for a reason here?

748
00:46:06,062 --> 00:46:07,229
She's not serious about him.

749
00:46:07,521 --> 00:46:08,854
She can't be.
Look at him.

750
00:46:09,437 --> 00:46:10,562
It's just Avani being Avani.

751
00:46:11,479 --> 00:46:14,729
Di, I can't have this conversation
with you in front of Vikram.

752
00:46:15,479 --> 00:46:17,104
You should have set boundaries earlier.

753
00:46:21,437 --> 00:46:22,771
I'm not done talking to you.

754
00:46:23,021 --> 00:46:25,437
- Avani, wait! Avani!
- Avani!

755
00:46:25,521 --> 00:46:26,812
- Close to the station?
- At the station.

756
00:46:26,896 --> 00:46:28,021
- Avani, are you serious?
- I'll call you.

757
00:46:28,104 --> 00:46:29,396
- Yeah, you do that.
- Avani, wait.

758
00:46:29,479 --> 00:46:30,354
- Call me.
- Okay?

759
00:46:30,437 --> 00:46:31,687
- Vikram, do something.
- Alright.

760
00:46:32,312 --> 00:46:33,687
- What?
- Let's go.

761
00:46:36,396 --> 00:46:37,521
- Avani.
- What's wrong?

762
00:46:37,646 --> 00:46:38,729
Can we just go, Flow?

763
00:46:39,896 --> 00:46:42,396
- Avani!
- Unbelievable!

764
00:46:49,062 --> 00:46:50,021
What happened?

765
00:46:51,229 --> 00:46:52,562
The vibe at home was tense.

766
00:46:58,062 --> 00:47:01,021
Di and Jeej found out about us.

767
00:47:02,271 --> 00:47:04,437
So? Big deal.

768
00:47:05,937 --> 00:47:06,896
You're unbelievable.

769
00:47:09,021 --> 00:47:09,896
I'm…

770
00:47:10,729 --> 00:47:11,604
pregnant.

771
00:47:26,812 --> 00:47:28,771
Do you want tea?

772
00:47:29,146 --> 00:47:30,396
No, Auntie.
I'm okay, thank you.

773
00:47:30,479 --> 00:47:31,979
Want some fried snacks?
I'll make it in two minutes.

774
00:47:32,062 --> 00:47:33,854
Why are you bugging her?

775
00:47:33,937 --> 00:47:34,937
She said no.

776
00:47:35,062 --> 00:47:37,312
Why are you getting annoyed?

777
00:47:37,396 --> 00:47:38,937
- Are you hungry?
- No.

778
00:47:39,021 --> 00:47:40,187
Auntie, I'm hungry.

779
00:47:40,354 --> 00:47:41,312
Then go home.

780
00:47:42,021 --> 00:47:42,937
Hello?

781
00:47:44,729 --> 00:47:45,687
I'm coming.

782
00:47:53,729 --> 00:47:54,646
What's the matter?

783
00:47:55,521 --> 00:47:56,521
How's the ride?

784
00:47:57,521 --> 00:48:00,021
- Avani wants to take off for a few days.
- Take off?

785
00:48:00,271 --> 00:48:02,312
A trip to Goa with you, homie.

786
00:48:04,479 --> 00:48:06,937
These are the keys to
the beach house in Goa.

787
00:48:07,354 --> 00:48:08,979
The caretaker knows you're coming.

788
00:48:11,521 --> 00:48:12,479
Also…

789
00:48:13,104 --> 00:48:15,271
Tara and Vikram want to talk to you.

790
00:48:16,312 --> 00:48:17,396
They're waiting downstairs.

791
00:48:17,562 --> 00:48:18,479
Here?

792
00:48:28,062 --> 00:48:29,812
- Jojo!
- Popo!

793
00:48:38,062 --> 00:48:39,021
Tara.

794
00:48:43,021 --> 00:48:43,979
Where's Avani?

795
00:48:45,021 --> 00:48:45,896
She's upstairs.

796
00:48:46,937 --> 00:48:48,979
And she's upset.
If she sees you two, she'll lose it.

797
00:48:49,104 --> 00:48:50,104
Yes, I know.

798
00:48:50,729 --> 00:48:52,646
That's why I wanted to talk to you.

799
00:48:53,729 --> 00:48:54,729
Look where you are.

800
00:48:55,479 --> 00:48:56,812
What the hell are you doing, Avani?

801
00:48:56,937 --> 00:48:58,146
Have you lost your mind?

802
00:48:59,896 --> 00:49:00,979
- Tea.
- No, thanks.

803
00:49:02,896 --> 00:49:04,521
- You?
- No.

804
00:49:04,729 --> 00:49:06,354
If you need anything, I'm inside.
Okay?

805
00:49:09,271 --> 00:49:10,812
Are you having his kid now?

806
00:49:11,354 --> 00:49:13,104
Are you going to pack snacks
for the rest of your life?

807
00:49:14,354 --> 00:49:15,521
Let's get real, Avani.

808
00:49:16,396 --> 00:49:17,646
I've spoken to Dr. Bhatia.

809
00:49:17,729 --> 00:49:19,729
- Once you're back from Goa…
- Whose idea was this?

810
00:49:21,021 --> 00:49:22,562
Yours, or Tara and Vikram's?

811
00:49:23,646 --> 00:49:24,812
How does that matter?

812
00:49:27,396 --> 00:49:29,146
We just want what's best for you.

813
00:49:30,771 --> 00:49:31,771
Okay, Lyra.

814
00:49:32,979 --> 00:49:34,812
I decide what's best for me.

815
00:49:35,812 --> 00:49:37,396
Not you.
Not Tara. Not Vikram.

816
00:49:39,104 --> 00:49:41,104
Avani goes through these phases.

817
00:49:41,771 --> 00:49:43,479
She's a kid,
she's not thinking straight.

818
00:49:44,271 --> 00:49:46,437
You're smart and sensible.

819
00:49:47,396 --> 00:49:48,271
I can tell.

820
00:49:48,854 --> 00:49:49,812
What do you mean?

821
00:49:50,146 --> 00:49:52,729
Just convince her to come home.

822
00:49:53,104 --> 00:49:54,021
Please.

823
00:49:55,021 --> 00:49:57,646
And we will take care of the situation.

824
00:49:58,187 --> 00:49:59,062
Situation?

825
00:50:00,646 --> 00:50:01,812
She's pregnant.
Just say it.

826
00:50:01,896 --> 00:50:03,312
- Talk to her.
- Tara…

827
00:50:03,979 --> 00:50:05,146
Why are we dragging this out?

828
00:50:06,021 --> 00:50:08,354
This is about money, right?

829
00:50:09,396 --> 00:50:10,312
Name your price.

830
00:50:11,187 --> 00:50:12,479
Consider it your fee or something.

831
00:50:13,187 --> 00:50:14,604
- Just get her to come home.
- Maruti!

832
00:50:15,021 --> 00:50:16,062
- We'll handle the rest.
- Maruti!

833
00:50:17,729 --> 00:50:19,146
What's going on?
Who is it?

834
00:50:19,229 --> 00:50:20,146
What's the matter?

835
00:50:20,354 --> 00:50:21,229
Who's he?

836
00:50:24,021 --> 00:50:24,937
A friend.

837
00:50:25,146 --> 00:50:26,354
- What?
- A friend.

838
00:50:27,979 --> 00:50:30,021
You go ahead.
Go. It's nothing.

839
00:50:37,729 --> 00:50:39,521
When a man knows his own worth,

840
00:50:40,896 --> 00:50:42,521
no amount of money
in the world can buy him.

841
00:50:44,062 --> 00:50:45,146
So, how are you going to afford me?

842
00:50:48,229 --> 00:50:49,354
Beat it. Go.

843
00:50:51,229 --> 00:50:52,729
Buzz off. Go away.

844
00:50:56,729 --> 00:50:57,687
He's just as crazy as she is.

845
00:50:58,104 --> 00:51:00,479
Hey, you, come here.

846
00:51:01,562 --> 00:51:02,729
Yes, I'm talking to you.

847
00:51:06,437 --> 00:51:07,396
What is it?

848
00:51:08,771 --> 00:51:10,687
Middle-class dreams often die…

849
00:51:11,729 --> 00:51:16,771
due to the arrogance of poverty.

850
00:51:18,187 --> 00:51:19,104
You know what?

851
00:51:19,896 --> 00:51:23,187
I used to dream of hearing
my voice on the radio.

852
00:51:24,021 --> 00:51:25,229
I wanted to be a singer.

853
00:51:26,271 --> 00:51:27,187
But I couldn't.

854
00:51:29,354 --> 00:51:30,271
I became a husband.

855
00:51:31,312 --> 00:51:32,521
And then a father.

856
00:51:33,312 --> 00:51:35,562
To carry that weight,

857
00:51:36,354 --> 00:51:37,312
I became a driver.

858
00:51:40,187 --> 00:51:41,521
I thought it was just a temporary thing,

859
00:51:44,187 --> 00:51:45,562
but I never realized

860
00:51:46,979 --> 00:51:48,562
when it became permanent.

861
00:51:58,271 --> 00:52:02,396
Are you going to be an artist
with a kid in your arms?

862
00:52:03,229 --> 00:52:06,521
Hold a crying baby in one hand,

863
00:52:06,937 --> 00:52:07,937
and a mic in the other?

864
00:52:09,271 --> 00:52:11,687
All this swagger

865
00:52:11,937 --> 00:52:17,979
will vanish in a snap,
once you see a wet nappy.

866
00:52:18,521 --> 00:52:20,771
And only the stench will remain…

867
00:52:21,187 --> 00:52:23,479
The stench of dying dreams.

868
00:52:28,854 --> 00:52:29,854
He gets it, ma'am.

869
00:52:31,437 --> 00:52:32,521
Don't worry.

870
00:52:52,479 --> 00:52:53,437
Rai Harrie…

871
00:52:54,771 --> 00:52:56,771
You ask who runnin' this?
It's 7Bantaiz.

872
00:52:56,854 --> 00:52:59,312
Your man is cut from a rare breed

873
00:52:59,396 --> 00:53:01,812
Baby girl, the whole world knows
My face and my creed

874
00:53:01,896 --> 00:53:04,229
Even the goons
In your city bow down at my feet

875
00:53:04,312 --> 00:53:06,729
My lane, my game, my fame
It's unmatched, it's elite

876
00:53:06,812 --> 00:53:09,229
Bros are asking that it's so crowded

877
00:53:09,312 --> 00:53:11,729
First you leave my hand
And then you say it's my fault

878
00:53:11,812 --> 00:53:14,229
I've contacts with all influential people

879
00:53:14,312 --> 00:53:16,687
My name is branded
Gold necklace is what I wear

880
00:53:16,771 --> 00:53:19,437
From zero to hero
From coals to diamonds

881
00:53:19,521 --> 00:53:22,104
I've counted all the stars

882
00:53:22,312 --> 00:53:24,687
Munna Bhai talk
Collar up Jackie Shroff

883
00:53:24,771 --> 00:53:26,521
I'm on top
Whatever I do is top notch

884
00:53:26,604 --> 00:53:28,812
Yeah, we bringing
All this fire outta Mumbai City

885
00:53:28,896 --> 00:53:31,437
Punjabi flow
Marathi boy and this song rocks

886
00:53:31,521 --> 00:53:33,979
Just like India's winning shot of '83!

887
00:53:34,062 --> 00:53:35,687
This is real hip hop
And not some nonsense

888
00:53:36,729 --> 00:53:38,854
Those who stand by me are special
Rest are inconsequential

889
00:53:38,937 --> 00:53:41,354
I can bring powerful people to tears
It's no mean feat for me

890
00:53:41,437 --> 00:53:43,854
Here, everything gets done slowly, slowly

891
00:53:43,937 --> 00:53:46,312
You ask who runnin' this?
It's 7Bantaiz

892
00:53:46,396 --> 00:53:48,812
Your man is cut from a rare breed

893
00:53:48,896 --> 00:53:51,229
Baby girl, the whole world knows
My face and my creed

894
00:53:51,354 --> 00:53:53,687
Even the goons
In your city bow down at my feet

895
00:53:53,771 --> 00:53:56,562
My lane, my game, my fame
It's unmatched, it's elite

896
00:53:59,312 --> 00:54:01,187
Bengali Baba calls it the curse of Saturn.

897
00:54:03,062 --> 00:54:03,937
Meaning?

898
00:54:06,104 --> 00:54:08,312
When your stars go astray,
you're helpless in every way.

899
00:54:08,562 --> 00:54:10,604
If you got something to say,
say it to my face.

900
00:54:13,896 --> 00:54:15,729
Police!

901
00:54:16,937 --> 00:54:17,896
Two-wheeler…

902
00:54:18,104 --> 00:54:19,896
- Sir.
- Parked near the road.

903
00:54:23,312 --> 00:54:24,187
What's the problem?

904
00:54:25,187 --> 00:54:26,062
Where are you from?

905
00:55:19,771 --> 00:55:22,354
Hey, listen, Pesky Tawde is outside.

906
00:55:22,479 --> 00:55:23,896
How long are you going to take?

907
00:55:24,021 --> 00:55:25,646
Look at this mess.

908
00:55:27,146 --> 00:55:28,896
Tell your boss to loosen his pockets.

909
00:55:29,687 --> 00:55:32,896
Or this pool's going
to look just like the lake outside.

910
00:55:33,271 --> 00:55:34,146
Get it?

911
00:55:34,229 --> 00:55:35,896
Then go swim with the fishes.

912
00:55:36,354 --> 00:55:37,562
Keep it down.

913
00:55:37,646 --> 00:55:38,896
Tawde will hear you.

914
00:55:39,187 --> 00:55:40,104
I will handle him.

915
00:55:40,187 --> 00:55:41,479
But wrap this up quickly.

916
00:55:41,562 --> 00:55:43,104
I got to drain the pool tomorrow.

917
00:55:47,646 --> 00:55:48,937
Such a headache.

918
00:55:49,521 --> 00:55:53,187
Why'd he show up
when I'm already swamped?

919
00:55:54,062 --> 00:55:55,104
Jai Hind, sir.

920
00:55:55,312 --> 00:55:56,187
Tell me,

921
00:55:57,021 --> 00:55:57,979
whose car is that?

922
00:55:58,521 --> 00:56:01,187
Well, I was going to tell you…

923
00:56:01,271 --> 00:56:02,771
- No, I mean…
- Not your boss's, right?

924
00:56:02,854 --> 00:56:04,771
No.

925
00:56:05,021 --> 00:56:06,854
- Is your license renewed?
- No, sir.

926
00:56:06,937 --> 00:56:07,854
- No?
- No.

927
00:56:08,604 --> 00:56:10,229
Then who are these new faces?

928
00:56:10,646 --> 00:56:11,521
For training?

929
00:56:11,604 --> 00:56:13,312
Last batch of the season, sir.

930
00:56:13,646 --> 00:56:14,937
They're leaving in the morning.

931
00:56:15,021 --> 00:56:16,854
I'll drain the pool
for maintenance, too.

932
00:56:18,187 --> 00:56:19,812
You said that last week.

933
00:56:20,479 --> 00:56:21,604
You playing me?

934
00:56:21,687 --> 00:56:22,646
No, sir.

935
00:56:22,771 --> 00:56:24,771
Promise this time.
Come tomorrow.

936
00:56:25,396 --> 00:56:26,562
The pool will be closed.

937
00:56:27,479 --> 00:56:28,562
Listen,

938
00:56:29,562 --> 00:56:30,562
if I come back

939
00:56:31,646 --> 00:56:33,812
and see anyone else with you,

940
00:56:34,979 --> 00:56:36,687
I'm going to lock all of you up.

941
00:56:36,771 --> 00:56:38,062
- Clear?
- Yes, sir.

942
00:56:39,479 --> 00:56:40,521
Full of crap.

943
00:56:41,187 --> 00:56:43,521
These are our guests.

944
00:56:43,937 --> 00:56:44,854
They've come from Mumbai.

945
00:56:45,437 --> 00:56:46,812
Their bike broke down.

946
00:56:47,521 --> 00:56:49,396
Give them a deluxe room.

947
00:56:50,062 --> 00:56:51,354
- Okay?
- Yes, sir.

948
00:56:51,896 --> 00:56:53,604
Madam, you can stay here.

949
00:56:54,021 --> 00:56:55,771
No issues.
It's safe.

950
00:56:55,979 --> 00:56:56,937
Okay?

951
00:56:57,687 --> 00:56:59,729
Call me if you need anything.

952
00:57:00,062 --> 00:57:01,396
- You have my number?
- Yes, I do.

953
00:57:02,062 --> 00:57:03,437
- Take good care of them.
- Sure, sir.

954
00:57:04,021 --> 00:57:04,896
Jai Hind, sir.

955
00:57:06,021 --> 00:57:07,021
Come,

956
00:57:07,687 --> 00:57:08,562
I'll show you the room.

957
00:57:09,354 --> 00:57:10,896
Come, brother.

958
00:57:11,229 --> 00:57:12,104
This way.

959
00:57:24,521 --> 00:57:26,437
I don't want to crowd the house.

960
00:57:27,896 --> 00:57:29,354
And what? Am I supposed to raise
my kid in a dump?

961
00:57:30,187 --> 00:57:31,562
What will I eat?
What will I feed them?

962
00:57:31,646 --> 00:57:33,562
This just got real, bro.

963
00:57:36,479 --> 00:57:39,146
Now I get why my dad left.

964
00:57:41,479 --> 00:57:43,396
He had two kids at 21.

965
00:57:43,854 --> 00:57:44,979
It must've scared the hell out of him.

966
00:57:45,562 --> 00:57:46,687
Is the kid yours?

967
00:57:47,104 --> 00:57:48,312
Are you sure?

968
00:57:48,396 --> 00:57:49,896
Stop talking trash.

969
00:57:51,229 --> 00:57:52,396
I'll slap the hell out of you.

970
00:57:54,021 --> 00:57:55,479
My Avani is loyal.

971
00:57:57,229 --> 00:57:58,854
And it is my baby.
It's just that I don't want to be a dad.

972
00:57:58,937 --> 00:58:00,354
Is that so hard to get?

973
00:58:00,521 --> 00:58:02,646
I got it.
But you explain it to her.

974
00:58:03,229 --> 00:58:05,104
Explain it with love.

975
00:58:05,562 --> 00:58:06,937
And let me know what she says.

976
00:58:07,271 --> 00:58:08,562
Okay, catch you later.

977
00:58:16,396 --> 00:58:18,979
You think I'm trapping you, Flow?

978
00:58:25,646 --> 00:58:27,062
It's not that.

979
00:58:31,771 --> 00:58:32,646
Then…

980
00:58:34,104 --> 00:58:35,729
Don't be so distant.

981
00:58:36,729 --> 00:58:37,979
We'll figure this out.

982
00:58:44,979 --> 00:58:46,896
Lyra gave the doctor's
number to Fabric.

983
00:58:49,729 --> 00:58:51,062
Should we go there after this trip?

984
00:58:56,229 --> 00:58:57,437
Do you really want to raise a child?

985
00:59:00,021 --> 00:59:01,062
Did I say that?

986
00:59:03,021 --> 00:59:04,146
You don't want to raise a kid,

987
00:59:04,229 --> 00:59:05,646
and you don't want to abort either.

988
00:59:07,354 --> 00:59:08,812
- Then what do you want?
- Nothing.

989
00:59:10,271 --> 00:59:12,896
You, Lyra, and Fabric already
planned it all out, right?

990
00:59:13,979 --> 00:59:14,854
What?

991
00:59:14,937 --> 00:59:17,146
Stop acting like you're concerned
and involved.

992
00:59:17,729 --> 00:59:18,854
So I'm acting?

993
00:59:19,937 --> 00:59:20,812
Where are you going?

994
00:59:54,771 --> 00:59:56,687
Are you okay?

995
00:59:58,771 --> 00:59:59,729
What?

996
01:00:01,562 --> 01:00:04,062
Are you okay?

997
01:00:06,937 --> 01:00:08,021
I am fine.

998
01:00:09,021 --> 01:00:10,271
Want a beer?

999
01:00:13,187 --> 01:00:15,229
A little bit, come on!

1000
01:00:23,187 --> 01:00:24,229
Congratulations.

1001
01:00:42,687 --> 01:00:45,604
No one and nothing is worth
burdening your heart like this.

1002
01:01:00,021 --> 01:01:03,979
Take a deep breath and just exhale all
that is bothering you.

1003
01:01:05,729 --> 01:01:09,396
Remember this.

1004
01:01:33,979 --> 01:01:35,854
Madam, maintenance is underway.

1005
01:01:36,729 --> 01:01:38,104
The pool's filthy.

1006
01:01:39,104 --> 01:01:40,229
What do you want for lunch?

1007
01:01:44,646 --> 01:01:46,354
Whatever you get.
I'm down with that.

1008
01:01:47,021 --> 01:01:47,937
I don't give a…

1009
01:01:49,396 --> 01:01:50,646
We don't have a kitchen here.

1010
01:01:50,771 --> 01:01:52,104
Stash it in the red cupboard.

1011
01:01:52,187 --> 01:01:53,229
We have to order in.

1012
01:01:53,312 --> 01:01:54,437
Tell me quickly so I can call.

1013
01:01:54,521 --> 01:01:57,562
Listen, just order two Chinese dishes
and be done with it.

1014
01:01:57,729 --> 01:01:58,646
Okay.

1015
01:01:59,104 --> 01:02:01,187
Tell me something.
Where's the nearest garage?

1016
01:02:01,646 --> 01:02:04,062
It's three kilometers out.
The mechanic is at the corner.

1017
01:02:04,312 --> 01:02:06,354
- Near the market?
- Yes.

1018
01:02:07,187 --> 01:02:08,146
- Sir.
- Yes?

1019
01:02:08,562 --> 01:02:10,354
- Tell madam to get out.
- Okay.

1020
01:02:10,437 --> 01:02:11,521
I got to drain the pool.

1021
01:02:11,604 --> 01:02:13,937
Police will come and chew me out.

1022
01:02:14,021 --> 01:02:15,312
- I'll let her know. Keep this.
- Please.

1023
01:02:15,396 --> 01:02:16,437
Please tell her.

1024
01:02:16,562 --> 01:02:17,771
- Sure.
- I'll bring your food.

1025
01:02:17,854 --> 01:02:18,771
Okay.

1026
01:02:20,646 --> 01:02:21,521
Ms. Vanity.

1027
01:02:22,229 --> 01:02:23,396
This isn’t your kitchen…

1028
01:02:25,562 --> 01:02:27,729
where a chef snaps his fingers,
and a buffet appears.

1029
01:02:28,604 --> 01:02:30,396
You've got to tell them what to order.

1030
01:02:31,354 --> 01:02:32,812
Don't throw shade at me, Flow.

1031
01:02:33,521 --> 01:02:35,187
I'm stuck here because
we took your bike.

1032
01:02:35,271 --> 01:02:37,229
Because you said
you needed a break.

1033
01:02:38,312 --> 01:02:40,771
In one second, my life went from Gully Boy
to Sairat.

1034
01:02:42,312 --> 01:02:44,812
I just hope your crazy Jeej hasn't
wiped out my family yet.

1035
01:02:46,396 --> 01:02:47,354
Oh, please.

1036
01:02:47,604 --> 01:02:48,854
Don't be so dramatic.

1037
01:02:50,187 --> 01:02:53,646
Besides, this isn't some inter-caste
or love-jihad romance drama.

1038
01:02:54,021 --> 01:02:54,937
Popo,

1039
01:02:55,354 --> 01:02:57,104
if I speak up now, she'll lose it.

1040
01:02:59,062 --> 01:03:01,229
You're Avani Shah,
and I'm Maruti Kadam.

1041
01:03:03,437 --> 01:03:07,271
Your family will have a bigger issue with
this poor Kadam than with some rich Khan.

1042
01:03:07,771 --> 01:03:10,021
Just go figure out how
we're moving forward, Maruti.

1043
01:03:10,146 --> 01:03:11,271
I'm already on it,

1044
01:03:12,021 --> 01:03:13,312
but you've got to get out
of the pool first.

1045
01:03:13,854 --> 01:03:15,271
Come to the garage with me.

1046
01:03:16,104 --> 01:03:18,937
Just admit you need cash
for bike repair.

1047
01:03:20,896 --> 01:03:21,937
Take it from my bag.

1048
01:03:38,187 --> 01:03:39,104
Look here…

1049
01:03:39,229 --> 01:03:40,354
Hello! Excuse me!

1050
01:03:40,937 --> 01:03:43,271
I only took this much.
Don't accuse me of looting you later.

1051
01:03:44,396 --> 01:03:46,771
And don't worry,
I'll pay you back when we return home.

1052
01:03:48,021 --> 01:03:48,979
You keep floating.

1053
01:03:49,937 --> 01:03:52,437
We're in deep shit,
and she wants to be a mermaid.

1054
01:04:17,521 --> 01:04:21,062
Now chin up and smile!
You’re gonna be fine!

1055
01:04:32,312 --> 01:04:38,104
You're my destination, my love

1056
01:04:38,312 --> 01:04:40,021
You're my--

1057
01:04:40,604 --> 01:04:41,937
Bapya, write this order down.

1058
01:04:42,187 --> 01:04:43,146
One fried rice.

1059
01:04:43,479 --> 01:04:44,896
Two chicken gravies.

1060
01:04:45,146 --> 01:04:46,271
Yeah, whatever works.

1061
01:04:47,312 --> 01:04:48,479
Yes, of course.

1062
01:04:49,062 --> 01:04:50,479
And add 500 extra for us.

1063
01:04:51,187 --> 01:04:53,104
Yeah, sure.
Guess it's your lucky day.

1064
01:04:53,604 --> 01:04:54,771
Stop whining.

1065
01:04:54,854 --> 01:04:56,146
We'll square it soon.

1066
01:04:56,562 --> 01:04:59,396
Let me handle the pump house.
It's a mess.

1067
01:04:59,521 --> 01:05:00,771
Send it fast.

1068
01:05:02,687 --> 01:05:04,312
This plumber is useless.

1069
01:05:06,229 --> 01:05:07,771
