Did you find a way out?

1301
01:28:16,646 --> 01:28:18,437
No, the water was too high.

1302
01:28:19,271 --> 01:28:20,312
So I didn't go any further.

1303
01:28:22,354 --> 01:28:24,604
- What do you mean you didn't go ahead?
- Means I didn't go ahead.

1304
01:28:25,854 --> 01:28:27,729
How many times have I told you?
I can't swim!

1305
01:28:32,146 --> 01:28:33,396
You go if you want to.

1306
01:28:36,521 --> 01:28:37,396
Fine.

1307
01:28:37,937 --> 01:28:38,812
I'll go.

1308
01:28:39,187 --> 01:28:41,854
You keep ranting, I'll go check.

1309
01:28:46,229 --> 01:28:47,104
Popo, quiet!

1310
01:28:49,854 --> 01:28:50,729
Popo!

1311
01:28:51,146 --> 01:28:52,021
Avani!

1312
01:28:52,104 --> 01:28:53,854
- Quiet, Popo.
- Avani! Avani!

1313
01:28:56,062 --> 01:28:57,021
What the hell is that?

1314
01:29:16,562 --> 01:29:17,521
Avani, get back.

1315
01:29:18,229 --> 01:29:19,687
Back up slowly.

1316
01:29:20,396 --> 01:29:21,729
I'm right here.
Don't worry.

1317
01:29:24,896 --> 01:29:26,854
Don't look at it.
Don't make eye contact.

1318
01:29:29,312 --> 01:29:30,271
Keep moving.

1319
01:29:35,396 --> 01:29:36,312
Keep moving.

1320
01:29:37,229 --> 01:29:38,521
Back up.
Avani, back up.

1321
01:29:43,812 --> 01:29:45,104
Move!

1322
01:30:04,646 --> 01:30:05,604
Stay back…

1323
01:30:12,979 --> 01:30:13,854
It's going…

1324
01:30:29,521 --> 01:30:30,562
Where did it come from?

1325
01:30:33,979 --> 01:30:35,521
Why did you open the drain?

1326
01:30:37,604 --> 01:30:40,062
We had to try something
to get out of here.

1327
01:30:40,979 --> 01:30:41,937
How was I supposed to know…

1328
01:30:43,396 --> 01:30:44,687
the Godzilla of the gutter
was hiding in there.

1329
01:30:54,812 --> 01:30:55,687
Flow.

1330
01:30:59,146 --> 01:31:00,687
Why isn't it attacking us?

1331
01:31:01,187 --> 01:31:02,729
No clue, I'm also confused.

1332
01:31:03,812 --> 01:31:06,604
In Khoon Bhari Maang,
it tore off Rekha's face in an instant.

1333
01:31:08,479 --> 01:31:10,229
- Khoon Bhari Maang?
- Yes.

1334
01:31:11,104 --> 01:31:13,854
I'm yours, my love

1335
01:31:14,729 --> 01:31:16,604
You're my beloved

1336
01:31:16,687 --> 01:31:17,896
An action thriller by Hrithik's dad.

1337
01:31:17,979 --> 01:31:19,104
Haven't you seen it on cable TV?

1338
01:31:19,604 --> 01:31:21,771
Flow, can you focus?

1339
01:31:22,104 --> 01:31:23,229
Yeah, just saying.

1340
01:31:24,271 --> 01:31:25,896
How do we get out?

1341
01:31:26,604 --> 01:31:28,396
Should've thought about
that before jumping in.

1342
01:31:29,604 --> 01:31:30,479
Quiet.

1343
01:31:31,521 --> 01:31:33,104
It didn't come because of my noise.

1344
01:31:33,562 --> 01:31:34,771
It came because
of the smell of your blood.

1345
01:31:38,729 --> 01:31:40,479
Should we try to escape
through the drain?

1346
01:31:42,021 --> 01:31:43,146
Wow! Genius!

1347
01:31:43,979 --> 01:31:45,104
And what if it follows?

1348
01:31:46,146 --> 01:31:47,021
No need.

1349
01:31:47,771 --> 01:31:48,729
Let's just sit tight.

1350
01:31:49,771 --> 01:31:50,937
Someone will show up, eventually.

1351
01:32:13,812 --> 01:32:17,854
The moonlight is grinning
How could I ever sleep?

1352
01:32:17,937 --> 01:32:21,896
She didn't meet me
But I'll definitely miss her

1353
01:32:22,062 --> 01:32:23,979
Let me live in her memories

1354
01:32:24,062 --> 01:32:29,396
Because she's miles away from me

1355
01:32:30,229 --> 01:32:34,229
The moonlight is grinning
How could I ever sleep?

1356
01:32:34,312 --> 01:32:38,312
She didn't meet me
But I'll definitely miss her

1357
01:32:38,437 --> 01:32:40,354
Let me live in her memories

1358
01:32:40,437 --> 01:32:45,812
Because she's miles away from me

1359
01:32:45,937 --> 01:32:48,187
You also smile a little

1360
01:32:48,312 --> 01:32:50,104
My life is so boring

1361
01:32:50,187 --> 01:32:52,312
Make it cheery

1362
01:32:52,396 --> 01:32:56,354
My dream is unfulfilled
Make it come true

1363
01:32:56,521 --> 01:33:02,187
I want to live
But you are far away from me

1364
01:33:02,646 --> 01:33:06,687
The little flowers have turned
Into withered leaves

1365
01:33:06,771 --> 01:33:11,062
I belong to her now
Her arrival has brought me to a halt

1366
01:33:11,146 --> 01:33:12,479
I no longer live in this world

1367
01:33:12,854 --> 01:33:14,979
I love you, but I don't say it to you

1368
01:33:15,062 --> 01:33:17,104
I don't cry copiously

1369
01:33:17,187 --> 01:33:19,104
In this black and white world

1370
01:33:19,187 --> 01:33:21,979
She was colorful and bright

1371
01:33:22,062 --> 01:33:23,646
At times her fault, at times mine

1372
01:33:23,729 --> 01:33:26,312
These are only filmy dialogues, though

1373
01:33:26,396 --> 01:33:28,396
She is my ride, it feels she is by my side

1374
01:33:28,479 --> 01:33:29,896
You're the only true one
Nobody by the side

1375
01:33:29,979 --> 01:33:31,812
Used to fly high, my kite

1376
01:33:31,896 --> 01:33:34,437
I remember all those wild nights
Wild nights

1377
01:34:03,187 --> 01:34:07,229
The moonlight is grinning
How could I ever sleep?

1378
01:34:07,312 --> 01:34:11,354
She didn't meet me
But I'll definitely miss her

1379
01:34:11,437 --> 01:34:13,312
Let me live in her memories

1380
01:34:13,396 --> 01:34:18,479
Because she's miles away from me

1381
01:34:30,521 --> 01:34:31,646
Avani, I think it's gone.

1382
01:34:34,521 --> 01:34:35,562
Looks like it's gone.

1383
01:34:38,187 --> 01:34:39,062
Avani!

1384
01:34:49,771 --> 01:34:50,687
What happened?

1385
01:34:51,146 --> 01:34:52,062
Are you okay?

1386
01:35:00,896 --> 01:35:01,812
Look over there.

1387
01:35:04,604 --> 01:35:05,729
She was pregnant.

1388
01:35:06,854 --> 01:35:08,562
That's why she didn't attack.

1389
01:35:09,646 --> 01:35:11,479
She just wants a safe space.

1390
01:35:15,021 --> 01:35:15,937
Safe space?

1391
01:35:16,646 --> 01:35:17,646
For whom?

1392
01:35:18,604 --> 01:35:19,687
She wants a safe space!

1393
01:35:23,021 --> 01:35:24,854
This is why I prefer beaches.

1394
01:35:25,396 --> 01:35:27,479
Pools are useless.

1395
01:35:31,771 --> 01:35:33,104
The sight of those eggs
is making me hungry.

1396
01:35:35,437 --> 01:35:36,354
What?

1397
01:35:42,437 --> 01:35:44,937
Have you trained Popo?

1398
01:35:45,687 --> 01:35:48,562
Sit, stand, fetch?

1399
01:35:49,479 --> 01:35:51,271
Can he order food online?

1400
01:35:52,604 --> 01:35:54,146
He's way smarter than you.

1401
01:35:54,646 --> 01:35:55,604
Oh really?

1402
01:35:58,146 --> 01:35:59,104
Let's test him then.

1403
01:36:00,396 --> 01:36:01,396
And see how smart he really is.

1404
01:36:11,354 --> 01:36:12,229
Popo!

1405
01:36:13,146 --> 01:36:14,854
Fetch the parcel.
Pick it up and throw it.

1406
01:36:15,479 --> 01:36:17,062
Popo!
Popo!

1407
01:36:18,354 --> 01:36:19,979
Pick up the box and throw.

1408
01:36:20,104 --> 01:36:21,604
- Pick up the box and throw.
- Come on, Popo.

1409
01:36:21,687 --> 01:36:23,312
- Pick up and throw, baby.
- Grab it with your mouth and throw!

1410
01:36:23,479 --> 01:36:25,479
- Pick up and throw.
- I'm telling him the same thing.

1411
01:36:25,729 --> 01:36:26,979
He understands me better.

1412
01:36:27,354 --> 01:36:29,062
What nonsense?
Popo!

1413
01:36:29,646 --> 01:36:31,229
- Yes, come on, baby.
- Pick up, pick up!

1414
01:36:31,312 --> 01:36:32,896
- Hey, you idiot. Not there, over here.
- Come on…

1415
01:36:33,396 --> 01:36:35,937
- Don't talk to him like that.
- That's how we show love in the hood.

1416
01:36:37,312 --> 01:36:38,229
Popo!

1417
01:36:38,521 --> 01:36:40,354
- Come, Popo. Yes, yes!
- Popo, look at me.

1418
01:36:40,437 --> 01:36:42,104
- Bring it to me.
- Come on, Popo.

1419
01:36:42,229 --> 01:36:43,396
Grab and throw, baby.

1420
01:36:43,479 --> 01:36:45,146
- Bring it to me.
- Come on, Popo.

1421
01:36:45,646 --> 01:36:47,062
- Yes, baby.
- Grab that box.

1422
01:36:47,187 --> 01:36:49,521
- Box. Grab it.
- Yes, Popo.

1423
01:36:49,854 --> 01:36:51,021
- Yes.
- Grab it.

1424
01:36:51,146 --> 01:36:52,437
- Come on.
- Popo!

1425
01:36:52,562 --> 01:36:53,437
Popo!

1426
01:36:53,646 --> 01:36:54,604
What?

1427
01:36:55,729 --> 01:36:57,729
- Yes. Jump, baby.
- Popo, grab it by your mouth.

1428
01:36:57,812 --> 01:36:58,812
- Yes, drop it.
- Yes.

1429
01:37:02,187 --> 01:37:03,562
- Back up, back up a little
- Come on, Popo.

1430
01:37:03,646 --> 01:37:05,312
- Tell him to back up.
- Yes.

1431
01:37:05,437 --> 01:37:07,646
Run! Take a run up!
Run and throw.

1432
01:37:07,729 --> 01:37:10,146
- Yes. Yes, you got this.
- Oh shit… we're done for!

1433
01:37:32,812 --> 01:37:33,771
Popo is really smart.

1434
01:37:35,437 --> 01:37:36,312
Shut up.

1435
01:37:44,146 --> 01:37:45,104
That's it for me.

1436
01:37:46,146 --> 01:37:47,896
I can't stay here waiting to die.

1437
01:37:49,812 --> 01:37:50,896
Let's get out of here.

1438
01:38:06,771 --> 01:38:08,021
Can you reach the light?

1439
01:38:08,187 --> 01:38:09,812
No, push me up.

1440
01:38:11,396 --> 01:38:12,854
You said you're 5'8"?

1441
01:38:12,937 --> 01:38:14,604
And you said you're 5'7".

1442
01:38:16,312 --> 01:38:17,312
Okay, forget that…

1443
01:38:18,354 --> 01:38:20,521
Reach for the light.

1444
01:38:20,896 --> 01:38:22,229
There's a crevice under it.

1445
01:38:22,812 --> 01:38:24,021
- See it?
- Yeah, but…

1446
01:38:24,687 --> 01:38:26,229
Then what?

1447
01:38:26,312 --> 01:38:28,771
Grab the light, then the crevice.

1448
01:38:28,854 --> 01:38:30,271
You can easily get
to the top from there.

1449
01:38:30,937 --> 01:38:32,854
Easy on my left shoulder, though.

1450
01:38:33,854 --> 01:38:35,104
On the count of three.

1451
01:38:36,021 --> 01:38:37,104
I'll push you up.
Got it?

1452
01:38:37,187 --> 01:38:38,604
- Okay.
- Okay.

1453
01:38:38,979 --> 01:38:39,854
Three.

1454
01:38:40,354 --> 01:38:41,229
Two.

1455
01:38:41,437 --> 01:38:42,437
One.

1456
01:38:55,812 --> 01:38:56,687
You good?

1457
01:39:05,271 --> 01:39:06,271
Come on, let's try again.

1458
01:39:20,229 --> 01:39:22,021
Avani, you've got to hurry!
She's coming this way.

1459
01:39:32,062 --> 01:39:33,479
Grab the crevice, Avani.

1460
01:39:37,812 --> 01:39:39,437
Hurry up!
Avani, please.

1461
01:39:41,146 --> 01:39:42,229
Smash the glass.

1462
01:39:43,896 --> 01:39:45,896
I can't hold on any longer, Avani!
Please hurry!

1463
01:39:48,312 --> 01:39:50,771
Hurry up, Avani!
Come on.

1464
01:39:52,854 --> 01:39:55,062
Avani, you've got to hurry up!
She's almost here!

1465
01:39:56,979 --> 01:39:58,812
She's too close, Avani.
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

1466
01:40:03,812 --> 01:40:05,187
Did you get a grip?

1467
01:40:19,354 --> 01:40:21,729
Avani, pull yourself up! Lift your legs…
Come on.

1468
01:40:24,312 --> 01:40:25,437
Hey!

1469
01:40:26,187 --> 01:40:27,229
Hey!

1470
01:40:27,604 --> 01:40:29,187
Hey!

1471
01:40:59,271 --> 01:41:00,146
Hey!

1472
01:41:09,437 --> 01:41:10,437
Hold on, Avani!

1473
01:42:33,146 --> 01:42:34,021
Flow…

1474
01:42:37,312 --> 01:42:38,187
Oh God.

1475
01:42:44,562 --> 01:42:45,437
How's your hand?

1476
01:43:13,937 --> 01:43:15,771
Put your weight on it and keep it steady.

1477
01:43:23,146 --> 01:43:25,229
Yeah, I've reached out
to all her friends in Goa.

1478
01:43:25,312 --> 01:43:26,979
Called all her favorite properties.

1479
01:43:27,312 --> 01:43:28,271
Nothing.

1480
01:43:28,354 --> 01:43:29,687
This is her last location.

1481
01:43:29,771 --> 01:43:31,396
Yeah, we're talking
to the cops right now.

1482
01:43:32,562 --> 01:43:33,771
I'll keep you updated.

1483
01:43:34,479 --> 01:43:36,937
Arjun, this is so not like Avani.

1484
01:43:37,437 --> 01:43:39,687
To go AWOL like this for 24 hours now.

1485
01:43:39,771 --> 01:43:40,812
Something's really wrong.

1486
01:43:41,271 --> 01:43:44,354
You dragged me here
as if I kidnapped them!

1487
01:43:44,437 --> 01:43:46,812
Our friend is also missing.
Did we blame you?

1488
01:43:46,896 --> 01:43:48,187
You're the last person he called!

1489
01:43:48,271 --> 01:43:50,979
But that call dropped!
I've been trying to tell that to the cops!

1490
01:43:51,062 --> 01:43:53,062
Sir, what's this?
Take what you want and let us go.

1491
01:43:53,146 --> 01:43:54,104
Hey, silence!

1492
01:43:54,604 --> 01:43:55,729
- What's this?
- Hey!

1493
01:43:56,521 --> 01:43:57,979
- What's your full name?
- Fabric.

1494
01:43:59,062 --> 01:44:00,146
Your real name!

1495
01:44:01,604 --> 01:44:02,771
Purushottam Dhamdhere.

1496
01:44:04,354 --> 01:44:05,396
Purushottam Dhamdhere.

1497
01:44:06,062 --> 01:44:06,979
Yes, hold on.

1498
01:44:08,729 --> 01:44:10,146
A team from the Goa Police is patrolling

1499
01:44:10,229 --> 01:44:12,271
and alerting every hospital, checkpoint,

1500
01:44:12,354 --> 01:44:14,146
and toll booth
along the Goa-Bombay highway.

1501
01:44:14,479 --> 01:44:17,812
Cyber team is triangulating
their last available location.

1502
01:44:18,604 --> 01:44:19,562
So, don't worry.

1503
01:44:19,812 --> 01:44:20,896
- Tara…
- Thank you.

1504
01:44:20,979 --> 01:44:22,312
We'll find them, okay?

1505
01:44:23,812 --> 01:44:25,937
I really want her to be safe.

1506
01:44:26,271 --> 01:44:27,937
- Don't worry, they're looking for her.
- One minute, bro.

1507
01:44:28,604 --> 01:44:29,521
Excuse me, madam.

1508
01:44:30,229 --> 01:44:31,396
Maruti is a solid guy.

1509
01:44:31,562 --> 01:44:33,521
Don't worry.
He's got her back.

1510
01:44:34,604 --> 01:44:35,896
You also chill.

1511
01:44:36,562 --> 01:44:37,562
Just wanted to say that.

1512
01:44:38,187 --> 01:44:39,646
Eat up. It's good.

1513
01:44:40,229 --> 01:44:41,187
We aren't going anywhere.

1514
01:44:41,771 --> 01:44:43,146
Let me know if you need cash.

1515
01:44:43,771 --> 01:44:44,687
Sorry.

1516
01:44:48,729 --> 01:44:50,021
What are you getting out of this?

1517
01:44:51,229 --> 01:44:52,771
What are you trying to prove?
Just tell me.

1518
01:44:56,562 --> 01:44:58,687
If you were me,
what would you do?

1519
01:45:02,187 --> 01:45:03,354
I wouldn't have a baby.

1520
01:45:06,729 --> 01:45:08,812
I have so much left to do, Avani.

1521
01:45:09,812 --> 01:45:11,437
I want to be someone, make it big…

1522
01:45:11,521 --> 01:45:12,896
Escape from my hellhole.

1523
01:45:14,396 --> 01:45:15,354
If I were you,

1524
01:45:15,437 --> 01:45:17,687
I'd appreciate that
we aren't ready for this baby.

1525
01:45:24,104 --> 01:45:27,437
You hooked up with me because you
wanted a thrill in your boring life.

1526
01:45:28,271 --> 01:45:30,604
Now this kid is your escape,
your new "project".

1527
01:45:31,187 --> 01:45:33,437
If you were a project to me,
then what was I to you?

1528
01:45:34,229 --> 01:45:37,146
You also used me
to escape your shitty life!

1529
01:45:38,896 --> 01:45:41,604
So please, stop acting like
you're real, and I'm fake.

1530
01:45:48,146 --> 01:45:49,604
You think I'm ready?

1531
01:45:51,396 --> 01:45:54,062
- You think I planned all of this?
- Then why are you doing this?

1532
01:45:56,562 --> 01:45:57,854
Why do you want the baby, Avani?

1533
01:45:59,979 --> 01:46:02,687
Listen, we can fake the fame
and the followers.

1534
01:46:02,771 --> 01:46:05,021
But parenting isn’t an act.
You have to do it for real.

1535
01:46:07,896 --> 01:46:09,521
Haven't you seen my mom and sister?

1536
01:46:10,312 --> 01:46:11,187
Yes.

1537
01:46:11,937 --> 01:46:12,812
I've seen them.

1538
01:46:13,896 --> 01:46:16,146
I've seen a lot of love
in that small house.

1539
01:46:16,229 --> 01:46:19,562
Oh, God!
Spare me the rich-kid drama.

1540
01:46:20,396 --> 01:46:22,812
Don't romanticize my poverty for me.

1541
01:46:25,479 --> 01:46:26,937
You live in 10,000 square feet.

1542
01:46:27,021 --> 01:46:28,396
With a pool.

1543
01:46:28,729 --> 01:46:30,521
We get one water tank
for the whole locality.

1544
01:46:34,437 --> 01:46:35,729
You have everything, Avani.

1545
01:46:36,937 --> 01:46:38,146
But you don't value it.

1546
01:46:46,896 --> 01:46:49,312
I have everything I don't want, Flow.

1547
01:46:53,979 --> 01:46:56,229
I'm alone in that
10,000 square feet home.

1548
01:46:58,396 --> 01:47:00,104
Maybe this baby…

1549
01:47:00,729 --> 01:47:02,854
Maybe I won't feel lonely anymore.
I don't know.

1550
01:47:04,437 --> 01:47:05,729
Maybe when it's here,

1551
01:47:06,396 --> 01:47:08,479
I won't miss my parents so much.
I don't know.

1552
01:47:13,396 --> 01:47:14,354
Exactly.

1553
01:47:15,896 --> 01:47:16,896
You don't know.

1554
01:47:18,646 --> 01:47:19,854
You don't know, Avani.

1555
01:47:21,937 --> 01:47:24,146
You're placing a huge bet
on this "maybe".

1556
01:47:27,562 --> 01:47:31,146
A baby won't fix your loneliness
or your issues.

1557
01:47:35,604 --> 01:47:39,396
Someday you'll find a deeper reason
to have a baby… not an excuse.

1558
01:47:42,812 --> 01:47:44,396
Till then, I'm with you.

1559
01:47:47,312 --> 01:47:48,396
I promise.

1560
01:47:50,479 --> 01:47:52,354
I'll stand by you like a one-man army.

1561
01:48:02,354 --> 01:48:04,937
Can't tell if it's rain or tears.
Damn it!

1562
01:48:46,521 --> 01:48:48,021
Nothing works in this dump!

1563
01:48:49,146 --> 01:48:50,979
Two ladders, both useless.

1564
01:48:52,562 --> 01:48:53,521
It's rusted.

1565
01:48:53,604 --> 01:48:55,479
Its screws are loose too.

1566
01:48:57,104 --> 01:48:59,437
If there were another ladder,
I'd manage to climb up.

1567
01:49:02,104 --> 01:49:04,854
What shoddy construction!
Shall we try again, Avani?

1568
01:49:04,937 --> 01:49:05,812
Flow!

1569
01:49:06,687 --> 01:49:07,646
- Flow!
- Yeah?

1570
01:49:08,479 --> 01:49:09,396
Flow.

1571
01:49:11,146 --> 01:49:12,062
Popo!

1572
01:49:15,562 --> 01:49:16,687
She's the same limping croc.

1573
01:49:17,812 --> 01:49:18,771
How the hell did it get up there?

1574
01:49:28,687 --> 01:49:29,729
She went down the drain, right?

1575
01:49:29,812 --> 01:49:31,187
She's heading for Popo.

1576
01:49:31,937 --> 01:49:33,437
There has to be a way
out through the drain.

1577
01:49:34,854 --> 01:49:35,854
Flow!

1578
01:49:36,396 --> 01:49:37,521
Avani, should we go check it?

1579
01:49:37,604 --> 01:49:38,479
- Flow!
- What?

1580
01:49:38,562 --> 01:49:39,854
She's heading towards Popo!

1581
01:49:45,021 --> 01:49:47,896
Yeah, we have to do something.
We've got to do something.

1582
01:49:47,979 --> 01:49:48,896
Let's go.

1583
01:49:54,646 --> 01:49:56,521
Popo! Come down.

1584
01:49:56,646 --> 01:49:58,062
- Popo!
- Get down here.

1585
01:50:22,229 --> 01:50:23,104
Popo!

1586
01:50:23,187 --> 01:50:24,062
Come on, Popo.

1587
01:50:24,146 --> 01:50:25,146
Look at me.

1588
01:50:26,562 --> 01:50:28,271
Popo, come on, come on.
Come on.

1589
01:50:32,646 --> 01:50:33,562
Come here.

1590
01:50:34,646 --> 01:50:35,562
Popo.

1591
01:50:36,646 --> 01:50:38,437
Popo, come here.
Come here.

1592
01:50:38,646 --> 01:50:40,729
Please, please, please, just jump.

1593
01:50:43,354 --> 01:50:45,021
Baby, come on, please, just jump.

1594
01:51:05,437 --> 01:51:06,479
Come on, come on.

1595
01:51:12,646 --> 01:51:13,812
Hurry up!

1596
01:51:57,229 --> 01:51:58,187
Flow!

1597
01:51:58,479 --> 01:51:59,396
Flow!

1598
01:51:59,687 --> 01:52:00,896
Please!

1599
01:52:05,354 --> 01:52:06,896
No!

1600
